thread.title: 'Walking Dead' tops cable, down from 2014

title: 'Walking Dead' tops cable, down from 2014
text:
Motorcycle-riding Daryl Dixon (Norman Reedus) leads a parade of walkers away from Alexandria in AMC's 'The Walking Dead.' (Photo: Gene Page, AMC)
4 CONNECT 53 TWEET LINKEDIN 1 COMMENT EMAIL MORE The Walking Dead topped last week's cable ratings chart with 14.6 million viewers for Sunday's Season 6 premiere, but it was down from 2014's record fall opener (17.3 million).
For the week, the top-rated AMC drama topped all cable shows, including NFL games and baseball playoffs, in viewers and dominated among advertiser-coveted young adults. Talking Dead , the chat show that analyzes each episode, averaged 5.7 million viewers, down from the 6.9 million for last fall's premiere. With that strong showing, it trailed only FX's American Horror Story: Hotel among non-sports cable programs in both categories.
